OL,6,FIn a statement, the householder said
OL,7,Fshe regarded herself as "collateral
OL,8,Fdamage". She appreciated the fear that
OL,9,Fwould have been caused to the intended
OL,10,Fvictim while detailing the fallout for
OL,11,Fherself and her own family.
OL,13,F"This attack on the house has greatly
OL,14,Ftarnished their love for the
OL,15,Fproperty," said prosecutor Gerard
OL,16,FRogerson.
OL,18,FThe victim now feels anxious about
OL,19,Fpeople approaching her house and is
OL,20,Fscared to leave her dog alone and the
OL,21,Fhouse unoccupied.
